Create a simple Supabase database structure with the following tables:

1. users
- id
- name
- email_or_phone
- role (parent or tutor)
- location
- created_at

2. tutor_profiles
- tutor_id (linked to users)
- subjects
- classes
- experience_years
- qualification
- teaching_mode
- availability
- bio
- profile_photo
- approval_status (pending / approved / rejected)

3. tuition_requests
- id
- parent_id
- tutor_id
- subject
- class
- message
- status (new / contacted / closed)
- created_at

Explain each table in plain English.
Keep it MVP-level only.
